description.en: The BAF (Building Automation Functions) model is a catalogue of generic control functions usually implemented by automation engineers.

bibliographicCitation.value: Pruvost. H. (2023): The BAF ontology - a formalization of generic building automation functions for heating, ventilation and air conditioning systems. https://w3id.org/baf.

comment.en: Parameter describe time-invariant values and settings of the respective control actor. Thus thay can be added dependent on the respective application logic.

comment.en: Placeholder concept to stipulate reuse of existing ontologies such as dbpedia or  	http://www.productontology.org/id/

It may be required to further annotate an Input, Output or Parameter with a specific Semantic Type. For example in building automation to differ between room air temperature or outdoor air temperature.
